  "texts": [
    "By contrast, the general model form illustrated in Eq. 8 is unconstrained, which is to say that its frequency parameters are independently specified.",
    "In some circumstances, the greater freedom offered by such a model may be advantageous-for example, many natural signals contain a degree of inharmonicity due to the geometry or stiffness of the resonating object.",
    "However, vastly fewer examples of differentiable unconstrained models exist in the literature than of their constrained counterparts.",
    "Nonetheless, Engel et al. (2020b) introduced a differentiable unconstrained additive synthesiser, which they applied to the task of monophonic pitch estimation in an analysis-by-synthesis framework.",
    "The differentiable unconstrained model follows the form in Eq. 8, with the omission of the initial phase parameter."
  ],
